script works really well right now. It quickly finds flagged tweets.

Added more search keywords. Removed some old commented out code.

search.py now looks through the tweets of the found users and prints the
url of the tweets containing any of the keywords in an array.

for users and parsing the csv file. Currently the code prints the id of
the first user search result for users with less than 5 results.
Made small changes to Mario's python script so it also saves last name.

Copied Mario's python file into the project. This file parses a csv file
